                    Saskatchewan's initial allocation dropped from approximately 8,000 nominations in 2024
                    to just <strong>4,761 for 2026</strong>‚Äîa reduction of nearly 50%. This scarcity has
                    prompted the province to implement strict sector-based prioritization.
                </p>

